            <title>[CASSANDRA-20203] Slash-star comments require escaping in AsciiDoc</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-20203</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The markup using slash-start comments in &lt;a href=&quot;https://cassandra.apache.org/doc/stable/cassandra/cql/definitions.html#comments&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;definitions.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Multi-line comments are also supported through enclosure within `/*` and&lt;br/&gt;
`*/`&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;is rendered without the star:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Multi-line comments are also supported through enclosure within / and /&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;this can be corrected by escaping the slash-star with three plus signs, i.e., &amp;#43;&amp;#43;&amp;#43;/*&amp;#43;&amp;#43;&amp;#43;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
